        <h2>Why It Matters</h2>
        <p>The successful commercialization of nuclear fusion would completely disrupt the $6 trillion global energy market. It promises virtually limitless, carbon-free baseload power, rendering fossil fuels obsolete and complementing intermittent renewable sources like wind and solar. Early positioning in the companies building the infrastructure for this transition could yield generational wealth, making it a critical thematic allocation for long-term investors.</p>
